FBIS3-29348 "dreas033_d_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-033 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Feb 1994 South Korea Government Dismisses Reports OW1702111194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1041 GMT 17 Feb 94 OW1702111194 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Seoul, Feb. 17 KYODO -- South Korean Government authorities on Thursday [17 February] dismissed press reports that Kim Chong-il, son and heir apparent to North Korean President Kim Il-song, has been seriously injured. Officials told KYODO NEWS SERVICE the South Korean Government has observed nothing unusual in North Korea, stressing that it is "quiet." "If anything had happened to Kim Chong-il, changes in the daily schedule, including celebrations for his birthday (on Wednesday), should have appeared," the officials said in dismissing the reliability of the reports. [passage omitted covered by previously filed material]
